radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation with no focal lesions and no biliary dilatation. The pancreas shows normal attenuation without lesions. The spleen is normal in size and attenuation. Normal adrenal glands. The kidneys are normal in size with a possible cyst in the left kidney. The stomach is unremarkable. Small bowel loops are normal. The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated up to 9 mm with no extraluminal air or fluid collection. The urinary bladder and distal ureters are unremarkable. No lymphadenopathy noted. No signs of vascular issues or osseous lesions.
